# .env.local — maintainer secrets for local dev
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
# Both `dev-chrome.sh` and `node dev-server.js` auto-load it on startup.
# Values set in the shell environment win over the file — drop an
# `export FOO=...` in your .bashrc if you want to override per-shell.
#
# Provision:
#   Oura     — https://cloud.ouraring.com/oauth/applications → create app
#   Withings — https://developer.withings.com/dashboard/ → register app
#   Polar    — https://admin.polaraccesslink.com/ → "Add new client"
# Set the same secrets on Vercel (Project → Settings → Environment Variables,
# mark Sensitive) so prod `/api/proxy` can exchange tokens too.

OURA_CLIENT_SECRET=
WITHINGS_CLIENT_SECRET=
ULTRAHUMAN_CLIENT_SECRET=
POLAR_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Fitbit + WHOOP use PKCE — no client secret needed. Only the client_id lives
# in the adapter registry.
#
# Apple Health is file-import — no credentials at all.

# ── Catalog deploy hooks (used by the getbased-tools editor's Deploy button)
# When set, /api/deploy-catalog runs two extra steps after writing
# data/recommendations.json: (1) git commit + push the catalog repo, then
# (2) POST a Vercel Deploy Hook to trigger a rebuild. Both are best-effort —
# missing config skips the step silently.
#
# CATALOG_GIT_REPO  — absolute path to the repo that owns the catalog file.
#                     Defaults to the repo containing the symlink target of
#                     data/recommendations.json (typically getbased-tools).
#                     Only needed when the auto-detect can't find it.
# CATALOG_COMMIT_MSG — override the commit message. Default: "catalog: deploy from editor"
# VERCEL_DEPLOY_HOOK_URL — Vercel → Settings → Git → Deploy Hooks → Create Hook
#                         (URL is the secret; treat it like a token)
CATALOG_GIT_REPO=
CATALOG_COMMIT_MSG=
VERCEL_DEPLOY_HOOK_URL=
